    Scope and Contents
Papers and tapes on University Week- Winter 1971-72 which focused on China (People's Republic Of China, 1949-  ) or Communist China.  Held on February 13 through 20, 1972, the wek was planned as a prelude to President Nixon's trip to Peking.  Consists of programs, memoranda, press releases, and other items on events and speakers, including Dr. Samuel Rosen, Dr. Ping-Chia Kuo, Peter Seybolt, Walter Judd, Chiao Chien, and Paul Findley.  Topics and subjects  of discussions included Chinese medicine and health care, economic policy and social change in China, educational revolution in China, Chines family systems, what about Communist China now, and the new U.S. China- policy.  
  
